                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "1a6754914edf3178d035d659ef01dd8d",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Concealable",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "This weapon is designed to be inconspicuous or easily concealed. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Stealth checks and DCs to hide or conceal a weapon with this trait.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 401,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "e3ebabe03e8190448c5d613bf42a41d2",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Concussive",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                      "aonid": 236,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "NPC Core",
                    "page": 50,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "These weapons smash as much as puncture. When determining a creature's resistance or immunity to damage from this weapon, use the weaker of the target's resistance or immunity to piercing or to bludgeoning. For instance, if the creature were immune to piercing and had no resistance or immunity to bludgeoning damage, it would take full damage from a concussive weapon. Resistance or immunity to all physical damage, or all damage, applies as normal.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 178,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "db3dcba30733bab63da3438275614311",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Fatal",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "The fatal trait includes a die size. On a critical hit, the weapon\u2019s damage die increases to that die size instead of the normal die size, and the weapon adds one additional damage die of the listed size.",
                "type": "trait",
                "value": "d10"
              },
              {
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "104d6fc2d1d7f97108e1e9b4be5089b1",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "range increments",
                    "aonid": 227,
                    "game-obj": "Rules",
                    "name": "range increments",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Range",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Bestiary pg. 17",
                      "aonid": 2,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Bestiary pg. 17",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Bestiary",
                    "page": 17,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "These attacks will either list a finite range or a range increment, which follows the normal rules for range increments.",
                "type": "trait",
                "value": "increment 60 feet"
              },
              {
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "15577d9931e0c744a9e12be2d087a290",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Reload",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 279",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 279",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 279,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "While all weapons need some amount of time to get into position, many ranged weapons also need to be loaded and reloaded. This entry indicates how many Interact actions it takes to reload such weapons. This can be 0 if drawing ammunition and firing the weapon are part of the same action. If an item takes 2 or more actions to reload, the GM determines whether they must be performed together as an activity, or you can spend some of those actions during one turn and the rest during your next turn.  \n  \nAn item with an entry of \u201c\u2014\u201d must be drawn to be thrown, which usually takes an Interact action just like drawing any other weapon. Reloading a ranged weapon and drawing a thrown weapon both require a free hand. Switching your grip to free a hand and then to place your hands in the grip necessary to wield the weapon are both included in the actions you spend to reload a weapon.",
                "type": "trait",
                "value": "1"
              }
            ],
